
[1]crier

   CRIER, CRYER, n. [See Cry.] One who cries; one who makes proclamation.
   The crier of a court is an officer whose duty is to proclaim the orders
   or commands of the court, to open or adjourn the court, keep silence,
   &c. A crier is also employed to give notice of auctions, and for other
   purposes.
